HEADWORD: Forbruise
<hw>For*bruise"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To bruise
sorely or exceedingly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All <qex>forbrosed</qex>, both back and side.</q>
